rows.label: tlk70000009_01_msg0001
rows.name:
Hey there, traveler! Could I ask you a
question?

rows.label: tlk70000009_01_msg0002
rows.name:
Like, at what age should a big brother
stop making a little bro's packed lunch
for him?

rows.label: tlk70000009_01_msg0003
rows.name:
Uhm... Sorry, that's kind of a strange
question to ask. You see, I've got this...
friend...whose big bro makes his lunch.

rows.label: tlk70000009_01_msg0004
rows.name:
I mean, the little bro... It's not like he's
a kid. I mean, he's grown... He can
take care of himself...

rows.label: tlk70000009_01_msg0005
rows.name:
He even has a job doing guard duty on
the gate. So he can make his own damn
pack lunch! I'm old enough, dammit!

rows.label: tlk70000009_01_msg0006
rows.name:
Ach! My friend, I meant. He's old
enough. But the big bro, he just keeps
waking up early to make these lunches.

rows.label: tlk70000009_01_msg0007
rows.name:
If he didn't waste his energy on all this
fussing, he could be moving up in the
world! I just don't get why he...ugh...
